wbim:annotation.wbim:annotationText: This process cannot terminate although it has no deadlock and no lack of synchronization. Instead, it has a livelock.
This process can terminate despite the inifinte loop because of the stop event which terminates the process by removing all tokens.
This process has a lack of synchronization.
This process has a lack of synchronization at the XOR-join because the OR-split can send multiple tokens over the branches.

This process has multiple input and output pinsets. The pinsets are overlapping.
The process has a deadlock on the first AND-split.
This process has multiple input and output pinsets. The pinsets do not overlap.
